"""
Config vs Export Files Comparison Tool
========================================

Reads a single "Input" Excel file (Inputs tab + Rate_Variables tab +
Column Match_Tr tab), compares a Config file's tabs against export files
(Radar, EQ, Territory [+ a supplemental Territory file], Roof Limit),
and produces a single output report workbook.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
KEY BEHAVIOURS (please confirm / correct once real files are tested):
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. ALL sheet-name and tab-name matching (Config tabs vs export tabs,
   "Inputs"/"Rate_Variables"/"Column Match_Tr" sheet lookups) is
   case-insensitive and ignores spaces/punctuation.
2. Header row for Radar, Territory, Roof Limit export tabs AND all Config
   tabs is assumed to be ROW 1. Only the EQ export file has the row
   1/2/3 header-offset behaviour (A1 empty -> row 2, A1 & A2 empty ->
   row 3).
3. EQ column matching no longer reads a "Column Match_EQ" sheet. It uses
   the hardcoded synonym list in EQ_COLUMN_SYNONYM_PAIRS below. Entries
   are grouped transitively -- e.g. "EQ Construction Type", "Earthquake
   Construction Type", "Construction Type", and "Construction" are all
   treated as the same field, because the pairs given chain them
   together. Same for "Rate" / "Rate per $1000" / "Factor" / "Expense
   Load". Edit EQ_COLUMN_SYNONYM_PAIRS directly to adjust.
3b. NEW: An EQ export sheet can contain MULTIPLE tables laid out side by
   side (a second table's headers starting up somewhere to the right of
   the first table, with no data in between). Only the FIRST table is
   read/compared -- reading stops at the first blank/empty header cell
   encountered after the detected header row, and every column from
   that point on (i.e. the next table) is discarded. This is handled by
   read_df_first_table() below, used only for the EQ file.
4. Radar column matching uses the hardcoded synonym list in
   RADAR_COLUMN_SYNONYM_PAIRS below (in addition to exact-name matches).
5. Territory: the Territory export file (Inputs!C57) is matched to
   Config's "R_L_Territory" tab via the "Column Match_Tr" mapping sheet,
   same as before. A NEW supplemental file (Inputs!C56, single sheet) is
   also read; its columns are assumed to match Config columns by EXACT
   name (no mapping needed) and are combined with the main Territory
   file's columns before comparing against Config.
   NEW: the two files are combined specifically by matching on their
   "Territory" column (present in both the main Territory export file
   and the C56 supplemental file, matched case/space/punctuation-
   insensitively) -- NOT on any arbitrary shared column name. If either
   file is missing a "Territory" column, columns are combined by row
   position instead as a fallback (a warning is printed in that case).
6. Roof Limit: column matching is by exact column name only (no
   mapping), unchanged.
   NEW: for the "Limit" column specifically, the value "No Limit" (as it
   may appear in Config) and "No Sub-limit" (as it may appear in the
   Roof Limit export file) are treated as equal values when comparing
   rows. See LIMIT_VALUE_SYNONYM_PAIRS below to add more equivalent
   value pairs if needed -- this only applies to columns that resolve
   to "Limit", not other columns.
7. Row matching = exact full-row equality across matched/mapped columns.
   Numeric values are rounded to the decimal places given in Inputs!C8
   before comparing (blank C8 = no rounding).
8. Whenever ANY column (on either side) can't be matched -- by exact
   name or via mapping/synonyms -- the detail sheet shows the FULL
   table (all rows, both sides) rather than a partial diff, with the
   unmatched column's header colored red. When all columns match, only
   the genuinely mismatched rows are shown.
9. Output file name: "Comparison_Report_<State>_<timestamp>.xlsx" saved
   to the output folder path given in the Inputs tab (C58).

Run:
    Edit INPUT_FILE_PATH below, then: python compare_tool.py
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
"""

